parts.text: What are results USA 2025 Gubenatorial election?

In the 2025 U.S. gubernatorial elections, Democrats won in both New Jersey and Virginia. Mikie Sherrill was elected governor of New Jersey, and Abigail Spanberger was elected governor of Virginia. These victories shifted the balance, resulting in 26 Republican governors and 24 Democratic governors nationwide.

args.request: USA 2025 Gubernatorial election results

response.result: In the 2025 U.S. gubernatorial elections, Democrats secured victories in both New Jersey and Virginia. Mikie Sherrill won the governorship in New Jersey, while Abigail Spanberger was elected as the governor of Virginia. These wins represent a shift in the partisan balance, with Democrats gaining one governorship and retaining another, resulting in 26 Republican governors and 24 Democratic governors nationwide after the elections. Both Sherrill and Spanberger achieved decisive wins, outperforming expectations and winning their respective races by double-digit margins. This election cycle marked the first time since 1985 that all gubernatorial races were decided by such a significant margin.
